"Harry!" [p]
She changes from looking completely exhausted and rushes over to me in an innocent, childlike way.[p]
"Glad you're OK."[p]
"Thank God you came back.[p]
I was scared to be here all alone."[p]
"I'm here now. [p]
I was worried, too.[p]
I'm real happy to see you."[p]
I lightly hug Lisa and gently draw away. [p]
I then speak while looking into her eyes.[p]
"Lisa, can you tell me how to get to the lake?"[p]
"The lake? [p]
You take Bachman Road."[p]
"The road's blocked."[p]
I recall what Cybil told me.[p]
"Well, that's the only way out there."[p]
"Are you sure?[p]
There's gotta be another way."[p]
Lisa places her hand on her chin and thinks for a bit. [p]
Then, her eyes open wide as if she has realized something.[p]
"Wait, I just remembered something."[p]
"What?"[p]
"There's a water works over by my old elementary school.[p]
It's been abandoned for years.[p]
There's an underground tunnel out there used for inspections, or something![p]
I remember hearing it runs all the way to the lake!"[p]
"Really?! You think I can get to the lake from there?"[p]
"I've never been down in there myself, so I'm not positive.[p]
Besides, it's all fenced off to keep people out."[p]
"If there's a chance, I've got to try."[p]
Lisa embraces me again just as I think that her face is beginning to look tearful.[p]
"Harry, don't go![p]
I don't want to be alone.[p]
It's so scary I can't stand it."[p]
This one room in an empty hospital.[p]
In this state in which monsters could kick in the door and enter at any time,[p]
she has no weapons with which to defend herself with.[p]
So her being gripped with fear is only natural.[p]
What should I do?[p]


